Iseme Kamau &amp; Maema Advocates affiliated with the multinational group DLA Piper has been honored for its role in advising the government on the medical equipment services project.The local law firm received the recognition for the project which is among the largest health sector Public Private Partnership deals in Africa. The DLA Piper Africa team comprising lawyers James Kamau from IKM and DLA Piper, UK, picked the Transportation and Infrastructure Team of the Year award at the 2016 African Legal Awards held in Johannesburg, South Africa.The Sh50 billion project involved the central procurement of supply, installation, testing, maintenance and lifecycle of medical equipment, training and construction, and fit out works at 94 hospitals.